<legaldoc><law type="constitution"><section><sectno></sectno><constitutionalsection chaptername="Constitution" statutenumber="III-26"><bookinfo>Reissue Revised Statutes of Nebraska</bookinfo><articlesectno>III-26</articlesectno><catchline>Privilege of members.</catchline><para>No member of the Legislature shall be liable in any civil or criminal action whatever for words spoken in debate.</para></constitutionalsection></section><source><para>Neb. Const. art. III, sec. 23 (1875). </para></source></law></legaldoc>